cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.CG, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a method for generating samples using deep neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG). The authors also demonstrate the effectiveness of their approach in generating natural images (cs.CV) and in two applications to light-transport simulation (cs.GR). The use of coupling transforms and one-blob encoding suggests a focus on computational geometry (cs.CG), while the optimization for Monte Carlo integration involves probability theory (cs.PR).
